column5: Very pleased to have finally purchased my own rig, its about time!  It is previously enjoyed but new to me.  I am looking forward to many hours on the water and many memories to come...
Awesome!! Go get it all slimed up!
nice rig for your first... now get some pics of fish in it...
Good lookin rig!  I bet you cant wait to get it wet!
very nice, when are they installing the console?
Nice boat!! Is that the Canadian model? I use to run a simialr rig, mine was black though. I loved it and Im sure you will too, Congrats!
So have you put a down payment on a steering wheel yet? Nice rig for sure you will have a good season to fish this year.    Art
Looks great and the mark of a great angler-----Tiller handle  This automatically qualifies you for your man card
Awesome looking rig !!! Looks like a good stable fishing platform Do like me and get her slimed. The locals like to see the slime pics  Enjoy it!  Paul

Yep, its a 2006 Canadian 18ft.  The engine is a 60HP Evinrude Etec.  Played with it a bit this weekend.  Once I had the trim dialed in correctly, it rode pretty good.  Scary fast, Im not used to that kind of power in a tiller but I will just have to get used to it.  I am looking forward to the walleye opener next weekend...
nice looking rig!  i am sure she will bring you years of enjoyment!  cheers!
Congrats! definately looks like it would move quick, be safe and have fun!
Nice setup man! Tiller is the way to go, now that you have all the extra room in the boat for da fishing
